OL,6,FHe added: "We operate a zero-tolerance
OL,7,Fpolicy towards any suggestion of
OL,8,Fdisorderly or inappropriate conduct.
OL,10,F"While we fully respect the right to
OL,11,Fdue process and a fair hearing, it
OL,12,Fwould not be appropriate for the
OL,13,Findividual to continue in her role at
OL,14,Fthis time."
OL,16,FA statement by Cheshire Police and the
OL,17,FCrown Prosecution Service said: "We
OL,18,Fwould like to remind everyone that
OL,19,Fcriminal proceedings against Clare are
OL,20,Flive and that she has a right to a
OL,21,Ffair trial.
